I started to make a booru and made some helper/wrapper functions, that I thought I could also contribute here.
This function for example creates WebWorker instances within the sandboxed iframe that every zite is run inside.
[code]
/**
 * Creates a WebWorker with the specified scripts run once in it's scope.
 * 'scriptsToLoadInWorkerScope': An array of paths to scripts that should all be run before the give script should be run. Libraries should be specified here. 
 * 'scriptToRun': Path to the actual script to be run in the worker.
 * 
 * @returns A Promise.
 * Resolved, if the WebWorker was successfully created.
 * Rejected, if the WebWorker could not be created.
 * @resolve: The worker object.
 * @reject: An string with details on the error.
 */
createWebWorker(scriptsToLoadInWorkerScope, scriptToRun){
	return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
		if(!(scriptsToLoadInWorkerScope instanceof Array)){
			reject("scriptsToLoadInWorkerScope is of type \"" + typeof(scriptsToLoadInWorkerScope) + "\" and not \"Array\".");
			return;
		}

		/*
		 * 
		 * All zites live in iframes, that due to zeronets design, must not give the 'allow-same-origin' permission in the iframe sandbox.
		 * because of that workers cannot load any js files, since the browser makes special urls for those files before loading them from this generated url.
		 * however that new url is considered as a same-origin request and thus not allowed by the iframe.
		 * As references see:
		 *  https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1260388
		 *  https://www.fxsitecompat.com/en-CA/docs/2016/loading-cross-origin-worker-now-fires-error-event-instead-of-throwing-worker-in-sandboxed-iframe-no-longer-allowed/
		 *  https://github.com/HelloZeroNet/ZeroNet/issues/1010
		 *  https://github.com/HelloZeroNet/ZeroNet/issues/140
		 *  http://www.html5rocks.com/en/tutorials/workers/basics/#toc-inlineworkers
		 */
		//as a workaround all workers must load their js files from a blob and a blob url.
		//this means all used libraries as well as the js itself must be gathered in string form, appended to each other in the correct order, converted to a blob and then converted to an blob url.

		let fileGetPromises = [];
		for(let i = 0;i<scriptsToLoadInWorkerScope.length;i++){
			fileGetPromises.push(this.cmdp("fileGet", {"inner_path": scriptsToLoadInWorkerScope[i], "required": true}));
		}
		Promise.all(fileGetPromises).then(
			(values)=>{
				this.cmdp("fileGet", {"inner_path": scriptToRun, "required": true}).then(
					(script) =>{
						let blob = "";
						for(let j = 0;j<values.length;j++){
							blob += values[j] + "\n";
						}
						blob += script
						blob = new Blob([blob]);
						values = undefined;//clear space
						script = undefined;//clear space
						let blobURL = window.URL.createObjectURL(blob);
						let w = new Worker(blobURL);
						resolve(w);
						return;
					},
					(error)=>{
						reject("Failed to get the script that was supposted to be ruunning in the WebWorker.");
						return;
					}
				);
			},
			() => {
				reject("Failed to get at least one of the scriptsToLoadInWorkerScope.");
				return;
			}
		).catch(
			()=>{
				reject("Failed to get at least one of the scriptsToLoadInWorkerScope.");
				return;
			}
		);
	});
}
[/code]
It just returns the worker instance. Usage example:
[code]
let libs = ["js/lib/jimp.min.js"];
this.createWebWorker(libs, "js/workerScripts/jimp-make-thumbnail.js").then(
	(w)=>{
		w.onmessage = (e) => {
			if(e.data.error){
				reject(JSON.stringify(e.data.error));
			}else{
				this.cmdp("fileWrite", {"inner_path": thumbnailPath, "content_base64": e.data.result}).then(
					()=>{
						//clean up.
						w.terminate();
						w = undefined;
						resolve(thumbnailPath);
					},
					(error)=>{
						//clean up.
						w.terminate();
						w = undefined;
						reject(error ? JSON.stringify(error): "");
					}
				);
			}
		};
		w.onerror = (error) => {
			reject(error ? JSON.stringify(error): "");
		}
		w.onmessageerror = (error) => {
			reject(error ? JSON.stringify(error): "");
		}
		w.postMessage({
			image: image,
			maxWidth: 500,
			maxHight: 250
		});
	},
	(error)=>{
		reject(error ? JSON.stringify(error): "");
	}
);
[/code]
This could, for example, be used for thumbnail generation or whatever causes loading long threads to freeze the browser.
